org.spf4j.stackmonitor
Class Sampler

java.lang.Object
  org.spf4j.stackmonitor.Sampler
All Implemented Interfaces:
ReportGenerator, SamplerMBean
@ThreadSafe
public final class Sampler
extends Object
implements SamplerMBean

Utility that allow you to sample what the application is doing. It generates a "Flame Graph" that allows you to quickly see you "heavy" operations. You can use JConsole to control the sampling while your application is running. By using a sampling approach you can choose your overhead. (sampling takes about 0.5 ms, so the default of 10Hz will give you 0.5% overhead) Collection is separated into CPU, WAIT and IO categories. I felt that most important is to see what hogs your CPU because that is where, you can most likely can do something about it.

Author:
zoly
